snippet: The Muslim Brotherhood said that around 57 percent of those who cast ballots voted for the proposed constitution, but opposition leaders said voting was marred by irregularities.
abstract: Supporters and opponents of Egyptian president Mohamed Morsi fight over preliminary results of referendum on draft constitution; Muslim Brotherhood says that roughly 57 percent of those who cast ballots voted for proposed constitution, but opposition leaders say voting was marred by irregularities; each side is seeking to frame results as favorable.

byline.original: By KAREEM FAHIM and MAYY EL SHEIKH

lead_paragraph: The Muslim Brotherhood said that around 57 percent of those who cast ballots voted for the proposed constitution, but opposition leaders said voting was marred by irregularities.

headline.seo: Egypt Votes on Constitution; Muslim Brotherhood Expects Approval
headline.main: First Round of Voting Spurs Dispute in Egypt
